  "assistantText": "✅ **Circuit built successfully!**\n\n## Wiring Summary\n\n| Component | Arduino Pin | Pin Name | Purpose |\n|-----------|-------------|----------|---------|\n| LED Red (+ series 220Ω) | **D11** | Signal | Red LED → toggle with Button 1 |\n| LED Green (+ series 220Ω) | **D10** | Signal | Green LED → toggle with Button 2 |\n| LED Blue (+ series 220Ω) | **D9** | Signal | Blue LED → toggle with Button 3 |\n| Button 1 | **D8** | Signal | Toggle Red LED |\n| Button 1 | **GND** | Ground | Button return |\n| Button 2 | **D7** | Signal | Toggle Green LED |\n| Button 2 | **GND** | Ground | Button return |\n| Button 3 | **D6** | Signal | Toggle Blue LED |\n| Button 3 | **GND** | Ground | Button return |\n\n## How It Works\n- Each button is wired with **INPUT_PULLUP**, so pressing pulls the pin LOW.\n- When a button is pressed, the sketch detects the LOW→HIGH transition and toggles the corresponding LED's state.\n- Each LED has a 220Ω series resistor to limit current (~20mA at 5V).\n- All buttons share the GND rail; all LEDs share the GND rail.\n\n**Press any button to toggle its LED on/off independently.** 🔴🟢🔵\n\nSafety note: Routed pin -3 through rail column -1 with one Arduino lead.",
